com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functor

Interface Profunctor<A,B>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - The type of the left parameter
    B - The type of the right parameter
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CheckedFn1<A,B>, Fn1<A,B>, Fn2<A,B,C>, Fn3<A,B,C,D>, Predicate<A>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    All, Any, CartesianProduct, Constantly, Cycle, Drop, DropWhile, Filter, FoldLeft, FoldRight, Id, InGroupsOf, Iterate, Map, Partial2, Partial3, ReduceLeft, ReduceRight, Repeat, Reverse, ScanLeft, Take, TakeWhile, Tupler2, Unfoldr, Zip, ZipWith
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Profunctor<A,B>
    A dually-parametric functor that maps contravariantly over the left parameter and covariantly over the right.

    For more information, read about Profunctors.

    See Also:
    Functor, Bifunctor, Fn1
